@see    TEP 102: Timers

Battery Voltage. The returned value represents the voltage at the Battery Sense pin (see ATRONschematics.pdf), which is (V_BATT * 10/64). Given two batteries at 3.7V each, its theoretical maximum is ~1.15V, but with fully charged batteries (~4.2V each) it can go up to ~1.3V.
(Which, translated into the 1023 = 5 Volt scale of the ADC converter, means that at most we will get ~260, or likely ~250 with fully charged batteries)
@author Mirko Bordignon

